{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:numbers.15",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "numbers",
    "chapterNumber": 15,
    "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15",
    "summary": "Source text for Numbers 15 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:1",
      "text": "And the Lord spoke to Moses, saying:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:2",
      "text": "Speak to the children of Israel and thou shalt say to them: When you shall be come unto the land of your habitation, which I will give you,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:3",
      "text": "And shall make an offering to the Lord, for a holocaust, or a victim, paying your vows, or voluntarily offering gifts, or in your solemnities burning a sweet savour unto the Lord, of oxen or of sheep:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:4",
      "text": "Whosoever immolateth the victim, shall offer a sacrifice of fine flour, the tenth part of an ephi, tempered with the fourth part of a hin of oil:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:5",
      "text": "And he shall give the same measure of wine to pour out in libations for the holocaust or for the victim. For every lamb,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:6",
      "text": "And for every ram there shall be a sacrifice of flour of two tenths, which shall be tempered with the third part of a hin of oil:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:7",
      "text": "And he shall offer the third part the same measure of wine for the libation, for a sweet savour to the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:8",
      "text": "But when thou offerest a holocaust or sacrifice of oxen, to fulfil thy vow or for victims of peace offerings,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:9",
      "text": "Thou shalt give for every ox three tenths of flour tempered with half a hin of oil,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:10",
      "text": "And wine for libations of the same measure, for an offering of most sweet savour to the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:11",
      "text": "Thus shalt thou do",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:12",
      "text": "For every ox and ram and lamb and kid.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:13",
      "text": "Both they that are born in the land, and the strangers",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:14",
      "text": "Shall offer sacrifices after the same rite.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:15",
      "text": "There shall be all one law and judgment both for you and for them who are strangers in the land.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:16",
      "text": "And the Lord spoke to Moses, saying:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:17",
      "text": "Speak to the children of Israel, and thou shalt say to them:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:18",
      "text": "When you are come into the land which I will give you,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:19",
      "text": "And shall eat of the bread of that country, you shall separate firstfruits to the Lord,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:20",
      "text": "Of the things you eat. As you separate firstfruits of your barnfloors:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:21",
      "text": "So also shall you give firstfruits of your dough to the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:22",
      "text": "And if through ignorance you omit any of these things, which the Lord hath spoken to Moses,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:23",
      "text": "And by him hath commanded you from the day that he began to command and thenceforward,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:24",
      "text": "And the multitude have forgotten to do it: they shall offer a calf out of the herd, a holocaust for a most sweet savour to the Lord, and the sacrifice and libations thereof, as the ceremonies require, and a buck goat for sin:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:25",
      "text": "And the priest shall pray for all the multitude of the children of Israel: and it shall be forgiven them, because they sinned ignorantly, offering notwithstanding a burnt offering to the Lord for themselves and for their sin and their Ignorance:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:26",
      "text": "And it shall be forgiven all the people of the children of Israel: and the strangers that sojourn among them: because it is the fault of all the people through ignorance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:27",
      "text": "But if one soul shall sin ignorantly, he shall offer a she goat of a year old for his sin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:28",
      "text": "And the priest shall pray for him, because he sinned ignorantly before the Lord: and he shall obtain his pardon, and it shall be forgiven him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:29",
      "text": "The same law shall be for all that sin by ignorance, whether they be natives or strangers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:30",
      "text": "But the soul that committeth any thing through pride, whether he be born in the land or a stranger (because he hath been rebellious against the Lord) shall be cut off from among his people:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:31",
      "text": "For he hath contemned the word of the Lord, and made void his precept: therefore shall he be destroyed, and shall bear his iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:32",
      "text": "And it came to pass, when the children of Israel were in the wilderness, and had found a man gathering sticks on the sabbath day,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:33",
      "text": "That they brought him to Moses and Aaron and the whole multitude.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.34",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:34",
      "text": "And they put him into prison, not knowing what they should do with him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.35",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:35",
      "text": "And the Lord said to Moses: Let that man die, let all the multitude stone him without the camp.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.36",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:36",
      "text": "And when they had brought him out, they stoned him, and he died as the Lord had commanded.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.37",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:37",
      "text": "The Lord also said to Moses:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.38",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:38",
      "text": "Speak to the children of Israel, and thou shalt tell them to make to themselves fringes in the corners of their garments, putting in them ribands of blue:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.39",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:39",
      "text": "That when they shall see them, they may remember all the commandments of the Lord, and not follow their own thoughts and eyes going astray after divers things,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.40",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:40",
      "text": "But rather being mindful of the precepts of the Lord, may do them and be holy to their God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:numbers.15.41",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "numbers",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Numbers 15:41",
      "text": "I am the Lord your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, that I might be your God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
